255
00:15:39.572 --> 00:15:42.406
I didn't go to Montauk to plan my
daughter's wedding to get that job.

256
00:15:42.475 --> 00:15:44.376
Do you know how
painful that was for me?

257
00:15:45.978 --> 00:15:48.277
But doesn't matter. really.
'cause you know what?

258
00:15:48.881 --> 00:15:50.247
No matter how hard I work.

259
00:15:50.316 --> 00:15:53.047
you always manage to
find a way to fuck my shit up.

260
00:15:53.119 --> 00:15:53.950
I said I was sorry.

261
00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:56.922
Well. if you want to apologize. why
don't you start with those women?

262
00:15:58.458 --> 00:16:01.223
How can I apologize. Helen.
when I didn't do anything?

263
00:16:01.294 --> 00:16:03.763
Oh. really? So they're all
lying? Why would they do that?

264
00:16:03.830 --> 00:16:06.061
I don't know. That's what
I'm trying to figure out.

265
00:16:06.132 --> 00:16:08.158
Oh. so you didn't sleep
with the student teacher?

266
00:16:09.302 --> 00:16:10.998
It was... it was consensual.

267
00:16:11.204 --> 00:16:13.264
Oh. except you were her boss!

268
00:16:13.339 --> 00:16:16.332
So maybe it didn't
feel consensual to her.

269
00:16:17.376 --> 00:16:19.607
Ugh. And what about Eden?

270
00:16:19.745 --> 00:16:21.805
She came to my room.
uninvited. and we made out

271
00:16:21.881 --> 00:16:23.577
for maybe fucking
one minute. that was it.

272
00:16:23.649 --> 00:16:24.660
But why did you let her in?

273
00:16:24.684 --> 00:16:26.983
Did you think maybe that
might have been a bad idea?

274
00:16:27.053 --> 00:16:28.997
- Because I was drunk.
- Well. whose fault is that?

275
00:16:29.021 --> 00:16:31.422
- Yours. actually! Yes.
- What?

276
00:16:31.491 --> 00:16:34.203
Earlier in the night. we went out. As
usual. you were drinking like a fish.

277
00:16:34.227 --> 00:16:35.126
You got me shit-faced.

278
00:16:35.194 --> 00:16:37.034
That was why I didn't
kick her out immediately!

279
00:16:37.063 --> 00:16:39.063
Are you seriously trying
to turn this around on me?

280
00:16:39.131 --> 00:16:42.659
Your inability to take responsibility
for your actions is pathological.

281
00:16:42.735 --> 00:16:44.829
- Oh. really? Really?
- Yeah. Yeah.

282
00:16:44.904 --> 00:16:47.840
Well. maybe 'cause I'm so busy
taking responsibility for yours!

283
00:16:48.541 --> 00:16:50.476
Oh. my God. Fuck you!

284
00:16:59.452 --> 00:17:02.718
I've done time for a crime I
didn't commit already. Helen.

285
00:17:03.155 --> 00:17:04.316
I'm not doing it again.

286
00:17:16.235 --> 00:17:17.601
Excuse me. What's going on?

287
00:17:17.670 --> 00:17:21.038
They're shutting down Sunset to
help with evacuations off the 405.

288
00:17:21.107 --> 00:17:22.451
You got to pull off
and turn around.

289
00:17:22.475 --> 00:17:24.876
No. I have to go to Brentwood
to get my kids at school.

290
00:17:26.512 --> 00:17:27.890
What do you mean?
I have to get through.

291
00:17:27.914 --> 00:17:30.292
They're about to start evacuating
the schools in Brentwood anyway.

292
00:17:30.316 --> 00:17:32.928
Well. if they're evacuating the
schools. then I really need to get through

293
00:17:32.952 --> 00:17:35.114
so I can. you know.
evacuate my children.

294
00:17:35.187 --> 00:17:36.450
Ma'am. I can't let you through.

295
00:17:36.522 --> 00:17:38.423
Dude. what the
fuck is your problem?

296
00:17:38.491 --> 00:17:39.959
- Helen.
- My kids are over there.

297
00:17:40.026 --> 00:17:41.703
- Helen. Helen. this is...
- I have to go get them.

298
00:17:41.727 --> 00:17:44.424
This isn't helping. Come on.
We'll figure something else out.

299
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:48.030
I'm sorry. okay? I
am. Let's just go.

300
00:17:54.574 --> 00:17:55.574
