308
00:18:28.674 --> 00:18:30.485
Can you call Whitney. see
what's up with her flight?

309
00:18:30.509 --> 00:18:32.501
Yeah. I'll check
in with Martin. too.

310
00:18:35.047 --> 00:18:37.107
- Priya.
- Oh. hi.

311
00:18:37.183 --> 00:18:40.551
Isn't he the most beautiful
baby you've ever seen?

312
00:18:40.886 --> 00:18:43.378
Yeah... he is beautiful.
yeah. Where's Sierra?

313
00:18:43.456 --> 00:18:46.119
Sierra is packing.

314
00:18:46.826 --> 00:18:48.317
- Hi.
- Hello?

315
00:18:48.661 --> 00:18:50.960
- Hi.
- Um. sorry.

316
00:18:51.197 --> 00:18:52.975
Uh. it was starting to
smell like smoke up here.

317
00:18:52.999 --> 00:18:55.644
I wanted to get Eddie out of the
hills. I didn't want to bother you guys.

318
00:18:55.668 --> 00:18:58.001
'cause you seemed kind
of busy. so I called Priya.

319
00:18:59.005 --> 00:18:59.836
Oh.

320
00:18:59.905 --> 00:19:03.307
They're going to stay with Abdul
and me until the smoke clears

321
00:19:03.376 --> 00:19:04.935
