00:59:28.331 --> 00:59:31.130
how this might affect other
people. besides my father?

953
00:59:36.706 --> 00:59:37.833
Yes. Whitney.

954
00:59:38.208 --> 00:59:42.441
I thought about it long and hard.
and I decided that it was worth it.

955
00:59:42.779 --> 00:59:43.779
Wow.

956
00:59:43.814 --> 00:59:46.443
Look. I worshipped your father.

957
00:59:46.883 --> 00:59:49.409
Okay? All I ever wanted
was to be a writer.

958
00:59:49.486 --> 00:59:51.717
and I'd read <i>Descent.</i>
like. a dozen times.

959
00:59:51.788 --> 00:59:55.418
so getting to study with
Noah Solloway was a dream.

960
00:59:55.492 --> 00:59:57.586
So you're mad at my father
because he didn't live up

961
00:59:57.661 --> 00:59:59.289
to your fantasies of him?

962
00:59:59.529 --> 01:00:00.861
No. that's not it.

963
01:00:01.965 --> 01:00:03.885
So. what is it. Audrey?
He didn't like your work?

964
01:00:04.768 --> 01:00:06.669
He didn't even give
my writing a chance.

965
01:00:06.736 --> 01:00:08.136
He took one look
at me and decided

966
01:00:08.205 --> 01:00:11.266
he knew how much I was worth
before he'd read a thing I'd written.

967
01:00:11.975 --> 01:00:12.975
Why would he do that?

968
01:00:14.511 --> 01:00:16.480
Because he didn't
respect me. Whitney.

969
01:00:16.947 --> 01:00:18.724
Well. maybe your writing
just wasn't very good.

970
01:00:18.748 --> 01:00:20.148
Did you ever consider that?

971
01:00:24.187 --> 01:00:25.587
Yeah. yeah. You're right.

972
01:00:25.989 --> 01:00:28.220
At the time. it-it
really wasn't.

973
01:00:29.593 --> 01:00:31.789
I was very young when
I was in Noah's class.

974
01:00:31.862 --> 01:00:34.855
and I was honestly
desperate for his guidance.

975
01:00:34.931 --> 01:00:39.096
but he didn't evaluate
my work. he evaluated me.

976
01:00:39.169 --> 01:00:41.001
He told me that I
had no inner life.

977
01:00:41.605 --> 01:00:42.605
Well. do you?

978
01:00:44.875 --> 01:00:46.605
Everyone has an inner life.

979
01:00:47.010 --> 01:00:51.448
What he meant was that
I didn't share his inner life

980
01:00:51.515 --> 01:00:54.679
and that I wasn't trying
hard enough to hide that.

981
01:00:55.252 --> 01:00:59.917
So. because I was writing about
being young and being female.

982
01:00:59.990 --> 01:01:02.687
he assumed that I had
nothing interesting to say.

983
01:01:03.827 --> 01:01:05.489
Have you ever experienced that?

984
01:01:07.931 --> 01:01:10.162
Look. it just sounds like
he was a shitty professor.

985
01:01:10.233 --> 01:01:11.677
and I'm sorry that
he hurt your feelings.

986
01:01:11.701 --> 01:01:14.102
but that's not a reason
to ruin his entire career.

987
01:01:14.304 --> 01:01:15.704
- It's not?
- No.

988
01:01:16.540 --> 01:01:17.540
Why not?

989
01:01:19.843 --> 01:01:21.334
Why didn't you
just drop the class?

990
01:01:21.978 --> 01:01:26.279
I did. Well. actually. first.
I complained to my dean.

991
01:01:26.349 --> 01:01:28.818
who told me that I needed
to grow a thicker skin.

992
01:01:28.885 --> 01:01:30.683
So. then I dropped the class.

993
01:01:30.754 --> 01:01:33.952
And it was a class that
I needed for my major.

994
01:01:34.024 --> 01:01:35.686
so I dropped that. too.

995
01:01:35.759 --> 01:01:39.457
And I stopped
writing for three years.

996
01:01:39.529 --> 01:01:42.226
and I went into a pretty
serious depression.

997
01:01:42.532 --> 01:01:45.696
That's terrible. Audrey. but
that's not my father's fault.

998
01:01:47.037 --> 01:01:48.505
So. whose fault is it?

999
01:01:49.673 --> 01:01:50.800
I don't know.

1000
01:01:51.107 --> 01:01:54.187
I don't think it's anybody's fault. I
think it's just something that happened.

1001
01:01:55.178 --> 01:01:57.306
Right. Okay. right.

1002
01:01:57.747 --> 01:02:00.478
That is exactly what I
thought. too. at the time.

1003
01:02:00.550 --> 01:02:05.250
But the truth is that the
way that Noah spoke to me.

1004
01:02:05.322 --> 01:02:07.120
the way that he treated me

1005
01:02:07.657 --> 01:02:12.459
confirmed my own
worst fears about myself.

1006
01:02:12.696 --> 01:02:15.894
Things that I had heard in one
way or another my entire life...

1007
01:02:15.966 --> 01:02:17.764
That I was worthless

1008
01:02:17.834 --> 01:02:22.169
and stupid and not hot enough.

1009
01:02:22.239 --> 01:02:24.902
just generally a waste of space.

1010
01:02:26.076 --> 01:02:28.807
And it really wasn't until I
started writing my memoir

1011
01:02:28.878 --> 01:02:31.780
that I even began to ask myself.

1012
01:02:31.915 --> 01:02:36.910
"Okay. why have I thought
this way all this time?

1013
01:02:37.120 --> 01:02:40.557
Why did I just assume
that the problem is me?

1014
01:02:40.624 --> 01:02:42.684
Why do I have to
leave the class?

1015
01:02:42.759 --> 01:02:46.287
And why is the way that Noah
treated me considered normal?"

1016
01:02:47.998 --> 01:02:49.899
Think about it. Whitney. okay?

1017
01:02:50.066 --> 01:02:54.333
We give men like him
such unbelievable rope.

1018
01:02:55.839 --> 01:02:57.774
We will do anything...

1019
01:02:58.074 --> 01:03:00.543
Anything... to
protect their egos

1020
01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:04.445
when they continuously
and carelessly destroy ours

1021
01:03:04.514 --> 01:03:05.447
without consequence.

1022
01:03:05.515 --> 01:03:08.144
I mean. why? Why does
it have to be like that?

1023
01:03:08.218 --> 01:03:09.550
I agree.

1024
01:03:09.619 --> 01:03:12.350
The world is a shitty
place. and it's not fair.

1025
01:03:12.489 --> 01:03:14.924
But I still feel like you're
using your private beef

1026
01:03:14.991 --> 01:03:16.789
with my father to
promote your book sales.

1027
01:03:16.860 --> 01:03:19.523
and that's just...
that's fucking bullshit.

1028
01:03:22.032 --> 01:03:23.032
Wow.

1029
01:03:25.268 --> 01:03:26.964
Someone really
did a number on you.

1030
01:03:28.271 --> 01:03:32.971
Look. I've had tough experiences
with older men. too... teachers. bosses...

1031
01:03:33.043 --> 01:03:35.376
But I'm adult enough to admit
that sometimes the problem

1032
01:03:35.445 --> 01:03:37.623
was just that I wanted to
fuck them and I shouldn't have.

1033
01:03:37.647 --> 01:03:39.411
Or I wanted them to
fuck me and they didn't.

1034
01:03:39.716 --> 01:03:41.036
Or maybe it's just
that sometimes

1035
01:03:41.084 --> 01:03:45.112
relationships between men and women
get weird and awkward. and that's normal.

1036
01:03:45.188 --> 01:03:47.054
But that doesn't mean
all men should burn.

1037
01:03:47.123 --> 01:03:49.183
Mm-hmm. Okay.

1038
01:03:50.293 --> 01:03:53.161
I wanted to sleep with
your dad. You're right.

1039
01:03:53.463 --> 01:03:56.797
And. yeah. he didn't want
to sleep with me back.

1040
01:03:56.866 --> 01:03:59.301
and that hurt my feelings.

1041
01:03:59.369 --> 01:04:02.897
But. Whitney. when you want
to sleep with these older guys.

1042
01:04:02.972 --> 01:04:06.033
ask yourself. like. what
are you really attracted to?

1043
01:04:06.309 --> 01:04:09.370
Is it them. or is it their power

1044
01:04:09.446 --> 01:04:12.541
and their authority.
their agency in the world?

1045
01:04:12.615 --> 01:04:15.744
Like. how they can
get the kind of shit done

1046
01:04:15.819 --> 01:04:17.515
that you can only dream of.

1047
01:04:17.587 --> 01:04:19.886
and they do it without
even breaking a sweat

1048
01:04:19.956 --> 01:04:23.518
because the world just offers
itself up to them on a silver platter.

1049
01:04:23.593 --> 01:04:26.620
Ask yourself. do you
really want to fuck them.

1050
01:04:26.863 --> 01:04:27.990
or do you want to be them?

1051
01:04:34.003 --> 01:04:35.904
I'm sorry about your family.

1052
01:04:36.306 --> 01:04:37.831
I really am.

1053
01:04:38.475 --> 01:04:43.106
And. yeah. I-I considered not
speaking up for this very reason.

1054
01:04:43.179 --> 01:04:45.375
'cause I thought...

1055
01:04:45.448 --> 01:04:49.579
"God. what if my individual
trauma is not worth blowing up

1056
01:04:49.652 --> 01:04:51.644
anyone else's life
in order to tell?"

1057
01:04:51.721 --> 01:04:54.919
But if we all do that.

1058
01:04:54.991 --> 01:04:56.823
if we all think like that.

1059
01:04:57.994 --> 01:05:00.293
then none of these stories
are ever gonna get told.

1060
01:05:00.830 --> 01:05:03.698
So. when does it become enough?

1061
01:05:04.768 --> 01:05:06.566
When does our
need to tell our stories

1062
01:05:06.636 --> 01:05:10.971
become greater than their
need to preserve the status quo?

1063
01:05:11.040 --> 01:05:13.874
Is it when we're abused
or when we're raped?

1064
01:05:13.943 --> 01:05:15.104
Or is that even enough?

1065
01:05:15.178 --> 01:05:17.807
Because. honestly. it depends
on the man in question. right?

1066
01:05:19.282 --> 01:05:22.377
Really. what I'm saying
is that this is the problem.

1067
01:05:22.986 --> 01:05:27.151
We constantly debate whether
we even have the right to speak.

1068
01:05:27.223 --> 01:05:31.718
Like. we. we monitor what
we say and our choice of words.

1069
01:05:31.795 --> 01:05:33.923
And. oh. are we sitting.
or are we standing?

1070
01:05:33.997 --> 01:05:36.262
And. oh. if we're sitting.
well. how are we sitting?

1071
01:05:36.332 --> 01:05:38.324
And if we're standing.
well. what are we wearing?

1072
01:05:38.401 --> 01:05:40.165
And are our voices
pitched just right?

1073
01:05:40.236 --> 01:05:41.876
I mean. think about
the mental gymnastics

1074
01:05:41.905 --> 01:05:45.069
that you have to do in order
to just have a conversation.

1075
01:05:45.375 --> 01:05:47.139
And now imagine
what it would be like

1076
01:05:47.210 --> 01:05:49.941
if we lived in a world where
we didn't have to do any of that.

1077
01:05:50.713 --> 01:05:52.375
Where we can just speak.

1078
01:05:54.217 --> 01:05:57.016
We're not the problem.
Whitney. They are.

1079
01:05:58.121 --> 01:06:00.784
All I want is just
to live in a world

1080
01:06:00.857 --> 01:06:03.486
where we're not. like.
weird second-class citizens

1081
01:06:03.560 --> 01:06:06.189
whose first job is to
make men comfortable.

1082
01:06:06.262 --> 01:06:08.390
and then we'll be
allowed to speak.

1083
01:06:13.503 --> 01:06:18.168
And. yeah. I think that your dad
is an impediment to that world.

1084
01:06:19.776 --> 01:06:22.143
And from what I
read in that article.

1085
01:06:23.012 --> 01:06:24.844
I'm not the only one.

1086
01:06:26.082 --> 01:06:27.106
So...

1087
01:06:28.351 --> 01:06:30.820
I felt that I needed to
say something. and I...

1088
01:06:32.255 --> 01:06:34.349
I just hope that you
can understand that.

1089
01:06:48.505 --> 01:06:49.529
She lives.

1090
01:06:50.773 --> 01:06:52.742
I told you my
flight was canceled.

1091
01:06:53.843 --> 01:06:55.573
Yeah. and then
you went radio silent.

1092
01:06:58.314 --> 01:06:59.782
I've been worried
about you. Whit.

1093
01:06:59.849 --> 01:07:01.511
I'm sorry. I'm so tired.

1094
01:07:01.584 --> 01:07:03.348
I had the craziest day.

1095
01:07:03.753 --> 01:07:05.051
I just need to go to bed.

1096
01:07:06.556 --> 01:07:08.388
- Wait a bit.
- Come on. Colin.

1097
01:07:13.096 --> 01:07:14.530
What's going on with you?

1098
01:07:14.764 --> 01:07:17.290
We barely spoke the entire
time you were in Montauk.

1099
01:07:26.276 --> 01:07:28.177
Nothing's going
on with me. Colin.

1100
01:07:28.244 --> 01:07:30.713
except for the fact that my
father just got Harvey Weinstein'd

1101
01:07:30.780 --> 01:07:33.375
and my whole future just
got flushed down the toilet.

1102
01:07:35.885 --> 01:07:38.166
And I don't really think I owe
you anything at the moment.

1103
01:07:38.221 --> 01:07:39.746
not even a conversation.

1104
01:07:39.822 --> 01:07:41.984
- I'm going to bed.
- I'm sorry. but you can't.

1105
01:07:42.058 --> 01:07:44.493
I know you've had a long day.
and I'm sure you're very tired.

1106
01:07:44.561 --> 01:07:45.790
but we have to talk.

1107
01:07:46.563 --> 01:07:49.226
You can't just disappear.
ignore my calls and texts.

1108
01:07:49.299 --> 01:07:50.460
That's not okay.

1109
01:07:50.867 --> 01:07:53.098
I'm about to be your
husband. for Christ's sake.

1110
01:07:59.442 --> 01:08:00.842
I can't do this.

1111
01:08:02.579 --> 01:08:04.445
You can't do what?
Can't talk to me?

1112
01:08:06.049 --> 01:08:07.415
I can't marry you.

1113
01:08:16.025 --> 01:08:17.025
Okay.

1114
01:08:19.362 --> 01:08:20.362
Why not?

1115
01:08:25.034 --> 01:08:26.696
'Cause I fucked someone else.

1116
01:08:47.357 --> 01:08:48.357
Who?

1117
01:08:50.393 --> 01:08:51.452
Furkat.

1118
01:08:52.528 --> 01:08:53.826
The photographer?

1119
01:08:54.297 --> 01:08:56.391
We used to date
back in New York.

1120
01:08:57.200 --> 01:08:58.200
What?

1121
01:08:59.168 --> 01:09:01.535
It only happened once.
that night at The Broad.

1122
01:09:05.642 --> 01:09:06.974
Were you with him today?

1123
01:09:07.176 --> 01:09:08.906
Yes. but nothing happened.

1124
01:09:10.413 --> 01:09:12.678
You don't have to believe
me. but it's the truth.

1125
01:09:16.653 --> 01:09:17.780
I believe you.

1126
01:09:26.996 --> 01:09:27.996
Do you love him. then?

1127
01:09:29.866 --> 01:09:32.961
No. He's an asshole.

1128
01:09:34.804 --> 01:09:36.670
But clearly. so am I.

1129
01:09:37.306 --> 01:09:38.968
You should leave me. Colin.

1130
01:09:39.575 --> 01:09:40.668
We should break up.

1131
01:09:43.913 --> 01:09:45.074
If that's what you want.

1132
01:09:46.282 --> 01:09:48.080
Why isn't it what you want?

1133
01:09:51.688 --> 01:09:54.214
I guess I'd like to know
what's going on first.

1134
01:09:55.792 --> 01:09:57.226
If we can fix things.

1135
01:09:57.960 --> 01:09:58.960
Right.

1136
01:10:00.263 --> 01:10:02.562
Right. because if we don't
fix things. you get deported.

1137
01:10:03.466 --> 01:10:04.729
Jesus!

1138
01:10:05.735 --> 01:10:09.763
Fucking Christ. Whitney. is that
really what you think this is about?

1139
01:10:10.273 --> 01:10:12.105
- A green card?
- Isn't it?

1140
01:10:12.175 --> 01:10:15.339
I hate this godforsaken country!

1141
01:10:16.145 --> 01:10:18.011
I'd love to go home!

1142
01:10:19.115 --> 01:10:20.879
I'm not with you because
I need a green card.

1143
01:10:20.950 --> 01:10:24.352
I need a green card because
I fucking want to be with you.

1144
01:11:09.165 --> 01:11:10.463
I'm sorry.

1145
01:11:13.503 --> 01:11:15.972
I know I'm an
impossibly slow painter.

1146
01:11:17.807 --> 01:11:22.245
I wish I could just turn out work
like some of my peers. like Furkat.

1147
01:11:22.445 --> 01:11:26.109
an-and sell them for millions
of dollars and buy us a house.

1148
01:11:27.049 --> 01:11:29.644
I will get there
someday. I know I will.

1149
01:11:30.153 --> 01:11:32.713
But just don't fucking
give up on me yet.

1150
01:11:32.789 --> 01:11:34.883
I'm so... I'm so sorry.

1151
01:11:35.825 --> 01:11:38.590
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1152
01:11:42.698 --> 01:11:44.530
I love you so much.

1153
01:12:00.016 --> 01:12:02.349
Whitney. you in there?

1154
01:12:02.618 --> 01:12:03.745
Whitney?

1155
01:12:07.523 --> 01:12:08.523
Oh. thank God.

1156
01:12:09.325 --> 01:12:10.325
What's up?

1157
01:12:10.526 --> 01:12:11.960
I'm sorry. uh. just showing up.

1158
01:12:12.028 --> 01:12:13.868
We didn't know where
you were. We were worried.

1159
01:12:13.896 --> 01:12:15.762
Oh. okay. well. I'm
fine. so you can leave.

1160
01:12:15.832 --> 01:12:19.234
No. I need to talk. I need to
talk. You've seen the news. right?

1161
01:12:20.703 --> 01:12:22.262
Of course. Uh...

1162
01:12:23.206 --> 01:12:25.539
Look. it's terrible. but I
need you to know there is...

1163
01:12:25.608 --> 01:12:27.076
that article. the allegations.

1164
01:12:27.143 --> 01:12:29.503
what those women are saying.
there is no truth in it at all.

1165
01:12:31.180 --> 01:12:33.308
Can I come in? Please?

1166
01:12:35.484 --> 01:12:36.484
Um...

1167
01:12:41.591 --> 01:12:44.925
Uh. Whitney. the-the
real story is-is...

1168
01:12:45.561 --> 01:12:47.039
it's just much. much
more complicated.

1169
01:12:47.063 --> 01:12:47.962
That doesn't matter.

1170
01:12:48.030 --> 01:12:50.795
The point is. I'm your
father and I love you

1171
01:12:50.867 --> 01:12:52.130
and you don't need to worry

1172
01:12:52.435 --> 01:12:54.563
because your mom and I.
we're gonna take care of this.

1173
01:12:55.037 --> 01:12:56.037
How?

1174
01:12:56.639 --> 01:12:58.839
- What do you mean?
- How are you gonna take care of it?

1175
01:12:59.408 --> 01:13:00.239
We're gonna fight it.

1176
01:13:00.309 --> 01:13:01.920
You really think that's
such a good idea?

1177
01:13:01.944 --> 01:13:03.207
Well. what choice have I got?

1178
01:13:03.279 --> 01:13:05.373
We're not gonna let
these women ruin our lives.

1179
01:13:07.316 --> 01:13:09.862
I'm so tired. I have to go to
sleep. I don't want to talk about it.

1180
01:13:09.886 --> 01:13:11.479
- I'm sorry.
- Whitney. I understand.

1181
01:13:11.554 --> 01:13:13.914
- I just need you to know...
- Mr. Solloway. it's very late.

1182
01:13:15.992 --> 01:13:16.992
You should go.

1183
01:13:18.261 --> 01:13:20.924
Hi. Colin. Hi. This
is. uh. no disrespect.

1184
01:13:20.997 --> 01:13:22.274
This is between
me and my daughter.

1185
01:13:22.298 --> 01:13:25.132
She doesn't want to talk to
you. She just asked you to leave.

1186
01:13:29.005 --> 01:13:30.769
- Oh. my God!
- Oh. God!

1187
01:13:31.007 --> 01:13:32.007
Whitney.

1188
01:13:33.142 --> 01:13:35.134
Oh. my God. we were
so worried about you.

1189
01:13:35.645 --> 01:13:38.581
- Uh. okay. Well. I'm fine.
- Okay.

1190
01:13:39.348 --> 01:13:42.318
Listen. I need to talk
to everybody. okay?

1191
01:13:42.385 --> 01:13:44.396
I found something out.
and I need to tell all of you.

1192
01:13:44.420 --> 01:13:46.286
so can we please
just sit down and talk?

1193
01:13:47.223 --> 01:13:48.223
Please?

1194
01:13:52.795 --> 01:13:57.290
Okay. uh. uh... all
of this is my fault.

1195
01:13:57.366 --> 01:14:00.165
Everything that's happening
right now is my fault.

1196
01:14:01.437 --> 01:14:02.437
What?

1197
01:14:04.573 --> 01:14:08.704
Because Sasha wants writing
credit for your dad's movie.

1198
01:14:09.378 --> 01:14:11.813
And I... he...

1199
01:14:12.281 --> 01:14:15.149
He used something I said
that I should not have said.

1200
01:14:15.217 --> 01:14:16.377
and he gave it to a reporter.

1201
01:14:16.419 --> 01:14:18.149
and now she's using
it against your father.

1202
01:14:18.220 --> 01:14:21.679
But your dad didn't do anything
wrong. They're just spinning it.

1203
01:14:21.757 --> 01:14:23.817
Can you take Stacey
and Trevor for ice cream?

1204
01:14:24.026 --> 01:14:25.137
- Yeah.
- We're not children.

1205
01:14:25.161 --> 01:14:26.601
- I want to stay.
- I need you to go.

1206
01:14:27.096 --> 01:14:28.257
Sure. yeah.

1207
01:14:28.698 --> 01:14:29.961
Ice cream sounds great.

1208
01:14:30.833 --> 01:14:31.926
Come on. Stace.

1209
01:14:34.003 --> 01:14:35.043
Hey. you sure you're okay?

1210
01:14:35.304 --> 01:14:36.465
- Yeah.
- All right.

1211
01:14:36.906 --> 01:14:37.999
Let's go. guys.

1212
01:14:41.344 --> 01:14:43.404
I'm not sure
exactly what I said.

1213
01:14:43.479 --> 01:14:45.958
but I think maybe it was that you
and Eden were sleeping together.

1214
01:14:45.982 --> 01:14:47.507
- Oh. Jesus. Helen.
- I'm sorry.

1215
01:14:47.583 --> 01:14:50.849
I-I really can't imagine that he would
do something like this. I'm really sorry.

1216
01:14:50.920 --> 01:14:52.889
- I'm so...
- Mom. why are you apologizing to him?

1217
01:14:53.990 --> 01:14:55.253
Because I fucked up.

1218
01:14:55.324 --> 01:14:56.917
How. exactly?

1219
01:14:57.226 --> 01:15:01.186
Uh. even if Sasha started it. does
that mean these women are lying?

1220
01:15:01.397 --> 01:15:04.390
Does that mean that Dad didn't
do the things he's being accused of?

1221
01:15:04.567 --> 01:15:06.763
You believe these women
over me? I'm your father.

1222
01:15:09.372 --> 01:15:10.897
Nobody's saying
that they're lying.

1223
01:15:10.973 --> 01:15:12.942
I'm just saying that
maybe they're exaggerating

1224
01:15:13.009 --> 01:15:14.009
what happened to them.

1225
01:15:14.410 --> 01:15:16.470
- Why would they do that?
- For attention.

1226
01:15:17.013 --> 01:15:19.005
I mean. these things
happen on a spectrum. okay?

1227
01:15:19.081 --> 01:15:23.382
Like. what they're describing is
awkward. yes. and uncomfortable. certainly.

1228
01:15:23.452 --> 01:15:24.452
It's not abuse.

1229
01:15:24.987 --> 01:15:28.253
And by calling it abuse. you
just turn women into victims.

1230
01:15:28.657 --> 01:15:31.889
And once you get older.
hopefully you will understand this.

1231
01:15:31.961 --> 01:15:34.761
Listen to yourself. Do you hear
yourself right now when you're talking?

1232
01:15:34.797 --> 01:15:38.131
He cheated on you. and he
left you. and he left all of us.

1233
01:15:38.300 --> 01:15:39.962
Why are you still defending him?

1234
01:15:40.036 --> 01:15:42.114
Because he's your father.
and you guys need your father.

1235
01:15:42.138 --> 01:15:45.336
Don't say that. This isn't about
us. This has never been about us.

1236
01:15:45.408 --> 01:15:47.206
- What is it about?
- You.

1237
01:15:49.812 --> 01:15:51.246
You could never let him go.

1238
01:15:51.547 --> 01:15:53.539
No matter what he did.
you forgave him for it.

1239
01:15:53.616 --> 01:15:55.244
That's not fair.

1240
01:15:57.119 --> 01:16:00.578
And it's not true. We got a divorce.
What more did you want from me?

1241
01:16:00.656 --> 01:16:02.249
I wanted you to condemn him.

1242
01:16:02.324 --> 01:16:05.817
I wanted you to admit to yourself
and to us what a shit he was

1243
01:16:05.895 --> 01:16:08.592
so that maybe I would have
an opportunity to acknowledge

1244
01:16:08.664 --> 01:16:10.895
that that behavior
wasn't normal!

1245
01:16:10.966 --> 01:16:13.401
So that maybe I wouldn't go
out looking for a guy to hurt me

1246
01:16:13.469 --> 01:16:15.062
the way that he hurt you!

1247
01:16:22.711 --> 01:16:24.009
That's what you think of me?

1248
01:16:28.851 --> 01:16:31.946
No. you don't understand.
This is all my fault.

1249
01:16:32.421 --> 01:16:33.946
None of it would have happened.

1250
01:16:34.190 --> 01:16:36.591
I mean. what those women
are saying. that's not...

1251
01:16:36.659 --> 01:16:39.458
it's not who your father is.

1252
01:16:45.334 --> 01:16:46.700
Mom. I believe them.

1253
01:16:51.307 --> 01:16:52.434
He did it to me.

1254
01:16:53.275 --> 01:16:54.504
- Whitney.
- What?

1255
01:16:55.444 --> 01:16:56.605
What are you talking about?

1256
01:17:00.216 --> 01:17:02.981
That night at Rodney
Callahan's party.

1257
01:17:03.452 --> 01:17:06.149
When you got in the hot
tub. you didn't recognize me.

1258
01:17:06.222 --> 01:17:08.953
But I saw the way
you look at women.

1259
01:17:13.996 --> 01:17:15.328
Like they're prey.

1260
01:17:16.165 --> 01:17:17.565
What is she talking about?

1261
01:17:19.869 --> 01:17:21.360
What is she talking about?

1262
01:17:26.742 --> 01:17:29.769
Noah. Noah.

1263
